cepts/inverted-index-81","page_id":"/en/docs/concepts/inverted-index","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/en/docs/concepts/inverted-index#why-inverted","content":"Mapping"},"664":{"id":"/en/docs/concepts/inverted-index-82","page_id":"/en/docs/concepts/inverted-index","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/en/docs/concepts/inverted-index#why-inverted","content":"Forward"},"665":{"id":"/en/docs/concepts/inverted-index-83","page_id":"/en/docs/concepts/inverted-index","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/en/docs/concepts/inverted-index#why-inverted","content":"Document ID → List of Terms"},"666":{"id":"/en/docs/concepts/inverted-index-84","page_id":"/en/docs/concepts/inverted-index","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/en/docs/concepts/inverted-index#why-inverted","content":"Inverted"},"667":{"id":"/en/docs/concepts/inverted-index-85","page_id":"/en/docs/concepts/inverted-index","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/en/docs/concepts/inverted-index#why-inverted","content":"Term → List of Document IDs"},"668":{"id":"/en/docs/concepts/inverted-index-86","page_id":"/en/docs/concepts/inverted-index","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/en/docs/concepts/inverted-index#why-inverted","content":"This inversion is what makes keyword-based search efficient. Instead of checking every document to see if it contains your query term, you jump straight to the term and get all matching documents immediately."},"669":{"id":"/en/docs/concepts/inverted-index-87","page_id":"/en/docs/concepts/inverted-index","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/en/docs/concepts/inverted-index#trade-offs","content":"While powerful, inverted indexes come with costs:"},"670":{"id":"/en/docs/concepts/inverted-index-88","page_id":"/en/docs/concepts/inverted-index","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/en/docs/concepts/inverted-index#trade-offs","content":"⚠️ Storage overhead: The index requires additional storage space."},"671":{"id":"/en/docs/concepts/inverted-index-89","page_id":"/en/docs/concepts/inverted-index","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/en/docs/concepts/inverted-index#trade-offs","content":"⚠️ Write amplification: Every write operation — INSERT, UPSERT, and UPDATE — require index maintenance, which adds latency to writes and increases I/O load."},"672":{"id":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-embedding","page_id":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-embedding","type":"page","content":"Vector Embedding","breadcrumbs":["User Guide","Introduction","Concepts"],"tags":[],"url":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-embedding"},"673":{"id":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-embedding-0","page_id":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-embedding","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-embedding#what-is-a-vector","content":"What is a Vector?"},"674":{"id":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-embedding-1","page_id":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-embedding","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-embedding#how-do-you-use-vectors-with-a-database","content":"How Do You Use Vectors with a Database?"},"675":{"id":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-embedding-2","page_id":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-embedding","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-embedding#how-vectors-power-real-world-applications","content":"How Vectors Power Real-World Applications?"},"676":{"id":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-embedding-3","page_id":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-embedding","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-embedding#what-is-an-embedding-model","content":"What is an Embedding Model?"},"677":{"id":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-embedding-4","page_id":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-embedding","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-embedding#types-of-vectors","content":"Types of Vectors"},"678":{"id":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-embedding-5","page_id":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-embedding","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-embedding#dense-vectors","content":"Dense Vectors"},"679":{"id":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-embedding-6","page_id":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-embedding","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-embedding#sparse-vectors","content":"Sparse Vectors"},"680":{"id":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-embedding-7","page_id":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-embedding","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-embedding#what-is-a-vector","content":"In the context of AI and vector databases, a vector is a list of numbers generated by embedding models to capture the semantic essence of unstructured data —  such as text, images, or audio."},"681":{"id":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-embedding-8","page_id":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-embedding","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-embedding#what-is-a-vector","content":"These models transform raw input into a high-dimensional space where semantically similar items produce similar vectors, enabling AI systems to compare meaning rather than relying on exact word matches."},"682":{"id":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-embedding-9","page_id":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-embedding","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-embedding#how-do-you-use-vectors-with-a-database","content":"🗂️ Store: Generate embeddings from your data — documents, product images, or user profiles — and save them in the vector database."},"683":{"id":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-embedding-10","page_id":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-embedding","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-embedding#how-do-you-use-vectors-with-a-database","content":"🔍 Search: When a new query arrives (a question, photo, etc.), generate a query vector using the same embedding model, then ask the database to find the most similar stored vectors."},"684":{"id":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-embedding-11","page_id":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-embedding","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-embedding#how-do-you-use-vectors-with-a-database","content":"Using efficient indexes, the database quickly returns relevant results — even at large scale. This is the foundation of semantic search: finding what means the same, not just what says the same."},"685":{"id":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-embedding-12","page_id":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-embedding","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-embedding#how-vectors-power-real-world-applications","content":"Image search is a great example:"},"686":{"id":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-embedding-13","page_id":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-embedding","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-embedding#how-vectors-power-real-world-applications","content":"Each image is converted into a vector that captures its visual features — such as shape, color, and object type."},"687":{"id":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-embedding-14","page_id":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-embedding","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-embedding#how-vectors-power-real-world-applications","content":"Images that are visually or semantically similar end up with nearby vectors."},"688":{"id":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-embedding-15","page_id":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-embedding","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-embedding#how-vectors-power-real-world-applications","content":"By comparing these vectors, systems can:"},"689":{"id":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-embedding-16","page_id":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-embedding","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-embedding#how-vectors-power-real-world-applications","content":"✅ Recognize the same person across different photos: Even with changes in lighting, pose, or expression, images of one individual generate similar vectors, allowing the system to match identities reliably."},"690":{"id":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-embedding-17","page_id":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-embedding","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-embedding#how-vectors-power-real-world-applications","content":"✅ Find look-alike products in e-commerce: When a user snaps a photo of a dress, lamp, or sofa, the system compares its vector to product vectors and retrieves items with similar appearance or style."},"691":{"id":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-embedding-18","page_id":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-embedding","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-embedding#how-vectors-power-real-world-applications","content":"All of this happens through fast vector similarity comparisons, powered by the vector database."},"692":{"id":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-embedding-19","page_id":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-embedding","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-embedding#what-is-an-embedding-model","content":"An embedding model is an AI model that converts raw data into vector embeddings — illustrated in the diagram at the top."},"693":{"id":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-embedding-20","page_id":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-embedding","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-embedding#what-is-an-embedding-model","content":"These models learn patterns from vast amounts of training data so that objects with similar meanings produce vectors that are close together in vector space — typically measured using distance metrics such as cosine similarity, dot product, or Euclidean distance."},"694":{"id":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-embedding-21","page_id":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-embedding","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-embedding#what-is-an-embedding-model","content":"className: text-base"},"695":{"id":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-embedding-22","page_id":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-embedding","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-embedding#what-is-an-embedding-model","content":"type: info"},"696":{"id":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-embedding-23","page_id":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-embedding","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-embedding#what-is-an-embedding-model","content":"The choice of distance metric matters. If an embedding model was trained for a specific metric (e.g., cosine similarity), the vector database should use the same metric during search to preserve semantic relationships and achieve optimal accuracy."},"697":{"id":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-embedding-24","page_id":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-embedding","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-embedding#what-is-an-embedding-model","content":"To explore and compare state-of-the-art embedding models, you can check out the Embedding Leaderboard on Hugging Face, which evaluates hundreds of models across diverse tasks and languages."},"698":{"id":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-embedding-25","page_id":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-embedding","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-embedding#types-of-vectors","content":"Vector representations are primarily categorized into two types: dense and sparse, each capturing data in its own way."},"699":{"id":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-embedding-26","page_id":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-embedding","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-embedding#dense-vectors","content":"Dense vectors are fixed-length, real-valued embeddings where (nearly) every dimension carries semantic information. These vectors are often generated by deep learning models that transform raw inputs (e.g., text, images, audio) into a structured vector space reflecting their semantic similarities."},"700":{"id":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-embedding-27","page_id":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-embedding","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-embedding#dense-vectors","content":"✅ Semantic-Rich: understands context and meaning (e.g., \"king – man + woman ≈ queen\")"},"701":{"id":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-embedding-28","page_id":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-embedding","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-embedding#dense-vectors","content":"⚠️ Opaque: hard to interpret which features drive similarity"},"702":{"id":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-embedding-29","page_id":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-embedding","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-embedding#sparse-vectors","content":"Sparse vectors are high-dimensional, often vocabulary-sized representations in which only a small subset of dimensions are non-zero. Each active dimension corresponds to a specific term (e.g., a word or n-gram), weighted by relevance scores such as BM25."},"703":{"id":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-embedding-30","page_id":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-embedding","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-embedding#sparse-vectors","content":"In this model, every document is converted into a vector — called a document vector — that records which terms appear in it and how important they are. Similarly, a search query is also turned into a sparse vector using the same weighting scheme."},"704":{"id":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-embedding-31","page_id":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-embedding","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-embedding#sparse-vectors","content":"Rather than relying on exact keyword matches, similarity between a query and a document is computed using the dot product of their vectors. This measures how well their weighted terms align: documents that contain the same important terms as the query receive higher scores — rewarding both term overlap and term importance."},"705":{"id":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-embedding-32","page_id":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-embedding","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-embedding#sparse-vectors","content":"For computational efficiency, sparse vectors use integer indices to map terms to their positions within a vocabulary dictionary rather than storing the term strings directly."},"706":{"id":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-embedding-33","page_id":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-embedding","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-embedding#sparse-vectors","content":"✅ Interpretable: non-zero dimensions map directly to known terms (e.g., 4017 → \"puppy\")"},"707":{"id":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-embedding-34","page_id":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-embedding","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-embedding#sparse-vectors","content":"⚠️ Lacks Semantic Understanding: treats \"car\" and \"automobile\" as unrelated unless explicitly linked"},"708":{"id":"/en/docs/data-operations/delete","page_id":"/en/docs/data-operations/delete","type":"page","content":"Delete","breadcrumbs":["User Guide","Working with Data","Data Operations"],"tags":[],"url":"/en/docs/data-operations/delete"},"709":{"id":"/en/docs/data-operations/delete-0","page_id":"/en/docs/data-operations/delete","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/en/docs/data-operations/delete#delete-by-ids","content":"Delete by IDs"},"710":{"id":"/en/docs/data-operations/delete-1","page_id":"/en/docs/data-operations/delete","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/en/docs/data-operations/delete#delete-by-filter-condition","content":"Delete by Filter Condition"},"711":{"id":"/en/docs/data-operations/delete-2","page_id":"/en/docs/data-operations/delete","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/en/docs/data-operations/delete","content":"Zvec provides two ways to delete documents. Choose the method that best fits your use case:"},"712":{"id":"/en/docs/data-operations/delete-3","page_id":"/en/docs/data-operations/delete","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/en/docs/data-operations/delete","content":"Method"},"713":{"id":"/en/docs/data-operations/delete-4","page_id":"/en/docs/data-operations/delete","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/en/docs/data-operations/delete","content":"Input"},"714":{"id":"/en/docs/data-operations/delete-5","page_id":"/en/docs/data-operations/delete","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/en/docs/data-operations/delete","content":"When to Use"},"715":{"id":"/en/docs/data-operations/delete-6","page_id":"/en/docs/data-operations/delete","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/en/docs/data-operations/delete","content":"delete()"},"716":{"id":"/en/docs/data-operations/delete-7","page_id":"/en/docs/data-operations/delete","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/en/docs/data-operations/delete","content":"One or more document ids"},"717":{"id":"/en/docs/data-operations/delete-8","page_id":"/en/docs/data-operations/delete","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/en/docs/data-operations/delete","content":"Use when you know the exact ID(s) of the documents you want to delete"},"718":{"id":"/en/docs/data-operations/delete-9","page_id":"/en/docs/data-operations/delete","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/en/docs/data-operations/delete","content":"delete_by_filter()"},"719":{"id":"/en/docs/data-operations/delete-10","page_id":"/en/docs/data-operations/delete","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/en/docs/data-operations/delete","content":"A filter expression (e.g., publish_year < 1900)"},"720":{"id":"/en/docs/data-operations/delete-11","page_id":"/en/docs/data-operations/delete","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/en/docs/data-operations/delete","content":"Use for bulk deletion based on field values — ideal for cleaning up documents that match specific criteria"},"721":{"id":"/en/docs/data-operations/delete-12","page_id":"/en/docs/data-operations/delete","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/en/docs/data-operations/delete","content":"className: text-base"},"722":{"id":"/en/docs/data-operations/delete-13","page_id":"/en/docs/data-operations/delete","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/en/docs/data-operations/delete","content":"type: warn"},"723":{"id":"/en/docs/data-operations/delete-14","page_id":"/en/docs/data-operations/delete","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/en/docs/data-operations/delete","content":"Delete operations are immediate and irreversible.Always double-check your input before running a delete operation."},"724":{"id":"/en/docs/data-operations/delete-15","page_id":"/en/docs/data-operations/delete","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/en/docs/data-operations/delete#delete-by-ids","content":"Assume you've already opened a collection and have a collection object ready."},"725":{"id":"/en/docs/data-operations/delete-16","page_id":"/en/docs/data-operations/delete","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/en/docs/data-operations/delete#delete-by-ids","content":"Use delete() to remove one or more documents when you know their exact IDs."},"726":{"id":"/en/docs/data-operations/delete-17","page_id":"/en/docs/data-operations/delete","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/en/docs/data-operations/delete#delete-by-ids","content":"className: text-base"},"727":{"id":"/en/docs/data-operations/delete-18","page_id":"/en/docs/data-operations/delete","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/en/docs/data-operations/delete#delete-by-ids","content":"type: info"},"728":{"id":"/en/docs/data-operations/delete-19","page_id":"/en/docs/data-operations/delete","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/en/docs/data-operations/delete#delete-by-ids","content":"When given a single id, delete() returns one Status object."},"729":{"id":"/en/docs/data-operations/delete-20","page_id":"/en/docs/data-operations/delete","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/en/docs/data-operations/delete#delete-by-ids","content":"When given a list of ids, it returns a list of Status objects in the same order."},"730":{"id":"/en/docs/data-operations/delete-21","page_id":"/en/docs/data-operations/delete","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/en/docs/data-operations/delete#delete-by-ids","content":"{\"code\": 0} indicates success."},"731":{"id":"/en/docs/data-operations/delete-22","page_id":"/en/docs/data-operations/delete","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/en/docs/data-operations/delete#delete-by-ids","content":"Non-zero codes indicate failure — for example, if the document id does not exist."},"732":{"id":"/en/docs/data-operations/delete-23","page_id":"/en/docs/data-operations/delete","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/en/docs/data-operations/delete#delete-by-filter-condition","content":"Use delete_by_filter() to remove all documents that match a boolean filter expression."},"733":{"id":"/en/docs/data-operations/delete-24","page_id":"/en/docs/data-operations/delete","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/en/docs/data-operations/delete#delete-by-filter-condition","content":"The filter can reference scalar fields (e.g., publish_year, language) using comparison and logical operators."},"734":{"id":"/en/docs/data-operations/fetch","page_id":"/en/docs/data-operations/fetch","type":"page","content":"Fetch","breadcrumbs":["User Guide","Working with Data","Data Operations"],"tags":[],"url":"/en/docs/data-operations/fetch"},"735":{"id":"/en/docs/data-operations/fetch-0","page_id":"/en/docs/data-operations/fetch","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/en/docs/data-operations/fetch","content":"Use fetch() to retrieve documents by their ids.This is a direct lookup — no search, scoring, or filtering is involved."},"736":{"id":"/en/docs/data-operations/fetch-1","page_id":"/en/docs/data-operations/fetch","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/en/docs/data-operations/fetch","content":"Input: A single document id or a list of document ids."},"737":{"id":"/en/docs/data-operations/fetch-2","page_id":"/en/docs/data-operations/fetch","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/en/docs/data-operations/fetch","content":"Output: A dictionary mapping each found id to its document."},"738":{"id":"/en/docs/data-operations/fetch-3","page_id":"/en/docs/data-operations/fetch","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/en/docs/data-operations/fetch","content":"Missing ids are silently omitted from the result (no error raised)."},"739":{"id":"/en/docs/data-operations/fetch-4","page_id":"/en/docs/data-operations/fetch","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/en/docs/data-operations/fetch","content":"The returned dictionary does not guarantee input order — access documents by id instead."},"740":{"id":"/en/docs/data-operations","page_id":"/en/docs/data-operations","type":"page","content":"Data Operations","breadcrumbs":["User Guide","Working with Data","Data Operations"],"tags":[],"url":"/en/docs/data-operations"},"741":{"id":"/en/docs/data-operations-0","page_id":"/en/docs/data-operations","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/en/docs/data-operations","content":"Zvec provides a complete set of data manipulation operations to manage documents in your collection."},"742":{"id":"/en/docs/data-oper