s":[],"type":"text","url":"/en/docs/data-operations/query","content":"The query() method supports vector similarity search, conditional filtering (like a SQL WHERE clause), or both combined in a hybrid query."},"1251":{"id":"/en/docs/data-operations/query-7","page_id":"/en/docs/data-operations/query","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/en/docs/data-operations/query","content":"It returns a list of Doc objects, each containing the matched document and its relevance score."},"1252":{"id":"/en/docs/data-operations/query-8","page_id":"/en/docs/data-operations/query","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/en/docs/data-operations/query","content":"className: text-base"},"1253":{"id":"/en/docs/data-operations/query-9","page_id":"/en/docs/data-operations/query","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/en/docs/data-operations/query","content":"type: info"},"1254":{"id":"/en/docs/data-operations/query-10","page_id":"/en/docs/data-operations/query","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/en/docs/data-operations/query","content":"Use VectorQuery objects for vector similarity search"},"1255":{"id":"/en/docs/data-operations/query-11","page_id":"/en/docs/data-operations/query","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/en/docs/data-operations/query","content":"Use a filter expression string (e.g., status = 'published') for conditional filtering"},"1256":{"id":"/en/docs/data-operations/query/multi-vector","page_id":"/en/docs/data-operations/query/multi-vector","type":"page","content":"Multiple Vectors","breadcrumbs":["User Guide","Working with Data","Data Operations","Query"],"tags":[],"url":"/en/docs/data-operations/query/multi-vector"},"1257":{"id":"/en/docs/data-operations/query/multi-vector-0","page_id":"/en/docs/data-operations/query/multi-vector","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/en/docs/data-operations/query/multi-vector#prerequisites","content":"Prerequisites"},"1258":{"id":"/en/docs/data-operations/query/multi-vector-1","page_id":"/en/docs/data-operations/query/multi-vector","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/en/docs/data-operations/query/multi-vector#performing-multi-vector-search","content":"Performing Multi-Vector Search"},"1259":{"id":"/en/docs/data-operations/query/multi-vector-2","page_id":"/en/docs/data-operations/query/multi-vector","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/en/docs/data-operations/query/multi-vector#re-ranking-strategies","content":"Re-ranking Strategies"},"1260":{"id":"/en/docs/data-operations/query/multi-vector-3","page_id":"/en/docs/data-operations/query/multi-vector","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/en/docs/data-operations/query/multi-vector","content":"Zvec supports multi-vector queries, allowing you to combine different embeddings in a single search."},"1261":{"id":"/en/docs/data-operations/query/multi-vector-4","page_id":"/en/docs/data-operations/query/multi-vector","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/en/docs/data-operations/query/multi-vector","content":"When querying multiple vector embeddings, Zvec retrieves top candidates from each vector space independently.Since similarity scores from different vector spaces might not be directly comparable, a re-ranker is required to fuse and and re-rank the results into a unified, relevance-ordered list."},"1262":{"id":"/en/docs/data-operations/query/multi-vector-5","page_id":"/en/docs/data-operations/query/multi-vector","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/en/docs/data-operations/query/multi-vector#prerequisites","content":"This guide assumes:"},"1263":{"id":"/en/docs/data-operations/query/multi-vector-6","page_id":"/en/docs/data-operations/query/multi-vector","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/en/docs/data-operations/query/multi-vector#prerequisites","content":"You have opened a collection with multiple vector fields"},"1264":{"id":"/en/docs/data-operations/query/multi-vector-7","page_id":"/en/docs/data-operations/query/multi-vector","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/en/docs/data-operations/query/multi-vector#prerequisites","content":"You're familiar with the basic vector querying concepts. If not, please review the single-vector search guide"},"1265":{"id":"/en/docs/data-operations/query/multi-vector-8","page_id":"/en/docs/data-operations/query/multi-vector","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/en/docs/data-operations/query/multi-vector#prerequisites","content":"This example collection contains two vector fields:"},"1266":{"id":"/en/docs/data-operations/query/multi-vector-9","page_id":"/en/docs/data-operations/query/multi-vector","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/en/docs/data-operations/query/multi-vector#prerequisites","content":"dense_embedding — A 768-dimensional dense vector using inner product metric"},"1267":{"id":"/en/docs/data-operations/query/multi-vector-10","page_id":"/en/docs/data-operations/query/multi-vector","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/en/docs/data-operations/query/multi-vector#prerequisites","content":"sparse_embedding — A sparse vector using inner product metric"},"1268":{"id":"/en/docs/data-operations/query/multi-vector-11","page_id":"/en/docs/data-operations/query/multi-vector","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/en/docs/data-operations/query/multi-vector#prerequisites","content":"It also includes two scalar fields (publish_year and category)."},"1269":{"id":"/en/docs/data-operations/query/multi-vector-12","page_id":"/en/docs/data-operations/query/multi-vector","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/en/docs/data-operations/query/multi-vector#performing-multi-vector-search","content":"To run a multi-vector search, pass a list of VectorQuery objects to the query() method and specify a fusion strategy via the reranker parameter."},"1270":{"id":"/en/docs/data-operations/query/multi-vector-13","page_id":"/en/docs/data-operations/query/multi-vector","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/en/docs/data-operations/query/multi-vector#performing-multi-vector-search","content":"This example queries both dense_embedding and sparse_embedding and uses a WeightedReranker to combine their results:"},"1271":{"id":"/en/docs/data-operations/query/multi-vector-14","page_id":"/en/docs/data-operations/query/multi-vector","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/en/docs/data-operations/query/multi-vector#performing-multi-vector-search","content":"className: text-base"},"1272":{"id":"/en/docs/data-operations/query/multi-vector-15","page_id":"/en/docs/data-operations/query/multi-vector","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/en/docs/data-operations/query/multi-vector#performing-multi-vector-search","content":"type: info"},"1273":{"id":"/en/docs/data-operations/query/multi-vector-16","page_id":"/en/docs/data-operations/query/multi-vector","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/en/docs/data-operations/query/multi-vector#performing-multi-vector-search","content":"In multi-vector search, topk takes on a different meaning compared to single-vector queries:"},"1274":{"id":"/en/docs/data-operations/query/multi-vector-17","page_id":"/en/docs/data-operations/query/multi-vector","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/en/docs/data-operations/query/multi-vector#performing-multi-vector-search","content":"topk (in query()): Controls how many candidate documents are retrieved from each vector field before re-ranking. A larger topk gives the re-ranker more candidates to work with, potentially improving final quality but increasing computational cost."},"1275":{"id":"/en/docs/data-operations/query/multi-vector-18","page_id":"/en/docs/data-operations/query/multi-vector","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/en/docs/data-operations/query/multi-vector#performing-multi-vector-search","content":"topn (in ReRanker): Controls how many final documents are returned after score fusion and re-ranking. This is your final result set size."},"1276":{"id":"/en/docs/data-operations/query/multi-vector-19","page_id":"/en/docs/data-operations/query/multi-vector","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/en/docs/data-operations/query/multi-vector#re-ranking-strategies","content":"Zvec provides different re-ranking strategies to combine scores from multiple vector fields."},"1277":{"id":"/en/docs/data-operations/query/multi-vector-20","page_id":"/en/docs/data-operations/query/multi-vector","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/en/docs/data-operations/query/multi-vector#re-ranking-strategies","content":"Re-ranker"},"1278":{"id":"/en/docs/data-operations/query/multi-vector-21","page_id":"/en/docs/data-operations/query/multi-vector","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/en/docs/data-operations/query/multi-vector#re-ranking-strategies","content":"WeightedReRanker"},"1279":{"id":"/en/docs/data-operations/query/multi-vector-22","page_id":"/en/docs/data-operations/query/multi-vector","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/en/docs/data-operations/query/multi-vector#re-ranking-strategies","content":"RrfReRanker (Reciprocal Rank Fusion)"},"1280":{"id":"/en/docs/data-operations/query/multi-vector-23","page_id":"/en/docs/data-operations/query/multi-vector","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/en/docs/data-operations/query/multi-vector#re-ranking-strategies","content":"Approach"},"1281":{"id":"/en/docs/data-operations/query/multi-vector-24","page_id":"/en/docs/data-operations/query/multi-vector","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/en/docs/data-operations/query/multi-vector#re-ranking-strategies","content":"Combines normalized similarity scores using custom weights"},"1282":{"id":"/en/docs/data-operations/query/multi-vector-25","page_id":"/en/docs/data-operations/query/multi-vector","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/en/docs/data-operations/query/multi-vector#re-ranking-strategies","content":"Fuses results based only on ranking positions — no scores needed  The RRF score at rank r is: \\text{RRF}(r) = \\frac{1}{k + r + 1}"},"1283":{"id":"/en/docs/data-operations/query/multi-vector-26","page_id":"/en/docs/data-operations/query/multi-vector","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/en/docs/data-operations/query/multi-vector#re-ranking-strategies","content":"Best for"},"1284":{"id":"/en/docs/data-operations/query/multi-vector-27","page_id":"/en/docs/data-operations/query/multi-vector","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/en/docs/data-operations/query/multi-vector#re-ran